// Regression: INT+PICK optimization must not over-consume tokens
// inside the if-handler's count=1 call. Per spec, `if` skips 2
// source tokens on the false path. When INT+PICK already consumed
// 2 tokens, the handler must not compile a third.
//
// Test 1 (false path): 0 → if skips `1` and `pick`, `drop` executes
// Test 2 (true path): 1 → `1 pick` executes (dup), then `drop`
: dup 1 pick ;
5 3 0 if 1 pick drop print
5 3 1 if 1 pick drop print
